commit.message:
lang: update plural tags definitions

This now includes CLDR and Weblate aliases to better deal with files not
using standard CLDR language codes. See
https://github.com/WeblateOrg/weblate/issues/11197

for more information, see https://pre-commit.ci

[pre-commit.ci] pre-commit autoupdate

updates:
- [github.com/astral-sh/ruff-pre-commit: v0.2.2 → v0.3.2](https://github.com/astral-sh/ruff-pre-commit/compare/v0.2.2...v0.3.2)

properties: fix mozila properties encoding space

This ancient workaround for Pootle is no longer needed.

Fixes #3232

tools: drop Mozilla l10n scripts

These are not maintained for years and no longer working.

Issue #4018

Fixes #880
Fixes #2472
Fixes #2473
Fixes #2471
Add support for i18next-v4 json files with different selectors via flat key handling

quote: handle all control chars equally

This make the behavior consistent for all control characters, not just
to these few defined.

Fixes #5199

lisa: strip characters which lxml will refuse to serialize

This consolidates behavior for all lxml based formats to strip
characters which would be rejected by lxml.

The previous behavior was:

- TMX stripped some of these since #4219 (issue #4183)
- XLIFF double escaped these as XML entities what is non-standard and
  not handled by any other XLIFF tools (introduced by #3551 and #3555)
- all other formats just crashed with ValueError: All strings must be
  XML compatible: Unicode or ASCII, no NULL bytes or control characters

This can be a breaking change in case somebody relied on the present
handling of control characters in XLIFF in translate-toolkit.

Fixes #3561

quote: performance improvements, code cleanups

- use lists to generate output and join in the end instead of building
  intermediate strings using +=
- use f-strings where applicable
- add type hints
